my puppy always sleeps i just got a jack russell terrior two days ago he is weeks old and all he dos is sleep he sleeps most of the night and during the day he lays around and sleeps i can pik him up and he falls back to sleep no matter what is this normal maggie puppies of course will sleep a lot however being that this is a jack russell we are talking about keep monitoring him they are about the most energetic dogs there are but if this keeps up at a chronic level have him checked he may have a health issue worthy of being checked out most puppies play a lot also at weeks and as they get older weeks etc but being lethargic is not good you may want to check with your breeder or other jack russell breeders or jr dog clubs and contact some owners better to be safe than sorry i hope the little fella' will be and is otherwise okay Dog breeding Labrador Retriever Mixed-breed dog Dog show Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Dog training Skinny Puppy Border Terrier Nintendogs German Shepherd Dog Breed registry Jack Russell Terrier Whippet Dog breed Dobermann American Pit Bull Terrier Havanese Guinea pig Puppy mill Housebreaking Docking Ferret The Tracey Ullman Show shorts English Springer Spaniel The Ashlee Simpson Show Beethoven (film) Basset Hound American Kennel Club Escape from New York Dog agility American Eskimo Dog Golden Retriever Hypertension Clinical depression Border Collie Irish Wolfhound Australian Cattle Dog Shetland Sheepdog Manx (cat) Dialysis Pet skunk Big Brother (USA TV series) Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Dean Koontz Sleeping Murder Cavalier King Charles Spaniel Nutrition Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Crate training Sick Puppy Ocean's Twelve Insomnia Cockapoo Maltese (dog) The Parting of the Ways Cat The Shining (film) Hip dysplasia Snoopy Pet store Boxer (dog) Tenterfield Terrier Scooby-Doo Narcolepsy Malaria Stroke Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Alaskan husky Soft-Coated Wheaten Terrier Tobacco smoking Trimipramine Honeybee EastEnders Smooth Collie Internet f